As fears mount of a third wave, many have criticized government for the slow rollout of the vaccines. The Covid-19 vaccine rollout is intensifying this week. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape Health Department says it has enough vaccines and capacity to vaccinate its elderly population. The department is attending to those with appointments and walk-ins. READ: COVID-19 Vaccine: Youths urged to help elders register The province has also intensified its rollout, increasing the number of vaccine sites available.